body:
Hello,
I'm getting ambiguous internal error on the code below. Here I wanted to use associative array or queue as a class type parameter.  It seems legal and works in major simulators.

The code:

```verilog
module test;
  class foo;
  endclass

  typedef foo foo_map_t[string];
  //typedef foo foo_map_t[$];

  class wrapper#(type VAL_T=int);
    VAL_T value;
  endclass

  initial begin
    wrapper#(foo_map_t) wrp = new();
    $finish();
  end
endmodule
```

The error:

```bash
$ verilator --binary test.sv && ./obj_dir/Vtest
%Error: test.sv:5:24: Internal: Unexpected Call
                    : ... note: In instance 'test'
    5 |   typedef foo foo_map_t[string];
      |                        ^
%Error: Internal Error: test.sv:5:24: ../V3AstNodeDType.h:472: Unexpected Call
                                    : ... note: In instance 'test'
    5 |   typedef foo foo_map_t[string];
      |                        ^
```

Verilator version: Verilator 5.023 devel rev v5.020-195-g6ffff8565
OS: Ubuntu 22.04.4 LTS
